WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:23.701 --> 00:00:28.020
♪ [ Woman Vocalizing ]

3
00:00:38.701 --> 00:00:43.020
[ Woman Narrating ]
Grandmother's house.

4
00:00:43.088 --> 00:00:46.724
Though it's been many years
since I last saw it.

5
00:00:46.791 --> 00:00:49.827
I'll always remember that
even my first impression...

6
00:00:49.894 --> 00:00:53.331
was one of fear and wonder.

7
00:00:55.066 --> 00:00:57.501
My childhood was
soon to be lost.

8
00:00:57.569 --> 00:01:00.037
my innocence shattered.

9
00:01:00.105 --> 00:01:03.107
and all our dreams destroyed...

10
00:01:03.174 --> 00:01:05.610
by what we would find within.

11
00:01:24.329 --> 00:01:27.998
♪ [ Vocalizing Continues ]

12
00:02:14.712 --> 00:02:17.348
My Mother and Father were
the center of my universe...

13
00:02:17.415 --> 00:02:19.350
when I was young.

14
00:02:19.417 --> 00:02:22.186
and I always wanted to grow up
to be just like mom.

15
00:02:26.842 --> 00:02:30.193
The whole family
was really close.
I still remember...

16
00:02:30.261 --> 00:02:34.115
how we'd greet dad
when he came home from
one of his many business trips.

17
00:02:34.182 --> 00:02:36.583
                He's home!

18
00:02:36.651 --> 00:02:38.585
Get Cory and Carrie.

19
00:02:38.653 --> 00:02:40.621
        Yeah.
        Come on. guys!
        Hurry up!

20
00:02:40.688 --> 00:02:42.723
[ Girl ]
Hurry!  Come on!
                    Daddy!

21
00:02:42.791 --> 00:02:46.294
        Come on. Carrie.
        Get behind the couch.

22
00:02:52.467 --> 00:02:55.219
            Get down.  Get down.
             get down. get down.

23
00:02:58.089 --> 00:03:00.408
        [ All ]
        Daddy!  Dad!

24
00:03:00.475 --> 00:03:05.112
        Yeah.  Yeah!
        How you doin'?

25
00:03:05.180 --> 00:03:07.981
[ Woman Narrating ]
He loved us all.
but dad never let me forget...

26
00:03:08.049 --> 00:03:09.967
that I was his favorite.

27
00:03:10.035 --> 00:03:12.219
     <i>[ Knock at Door ]</i>

28
00:03:16.991 --> 00:03:19.193
I was afraid the others
might be jealous.

29
00:03:19.260 --> 00:03:21.629
so I had to wait
until they all went to bed.

30
00:03:26.000 --> 00:03:29.136
                But you give me
                so much.
    Shh.

31
00:03:29.204 --> 00:03:31.305
Just tell me
what you think.

32
00:03:36.978 --> 00:03:41.349
                            ♪

33
00:03:41.416 --> 00:03:43.351
And you see?

34
00:03:43.418 --> 00:03:46.053
It's a jewel box
as well.

35
00:03:58.132 --> 00:04:00.934
The moment I saw that box.
I knew you had to have it.

36
00:04:02.937 --> 00:04:04.938
                    Oh!

37
00:04:18.653 --> 00:04:21.922
Mother. how should I
arrange the candles?

38
00:04:21.990 --> 00:04:24.792
I can have six rows of six
or three rows of 12.

39
00:04:24.860 --> 00:04:27.828
Or just one big circle
of 36 all around the cake.

40
00:04:27.896 --> 00:04:31.064
    What happened to two lines
    of 18?  Couldn't you
    figure that one out?

41
00:04:31.132 --> 00:04:34.001
        We want to taste
        daddy's cake!

42
00:04:34.068 --> 00:04:36.036
We want to taste
icing.

43
00:04:36.104 --> 00:04:38.806
        And lick the bowl!
And the spoon too!

44
00:04:38.874 --> 00:04:41.475
    Don't you look handsome
    and pretty?  But we have
    to wait until we sing...

45
00:04:41.543 --> 00:04:44.244
    "Happy Birthday" to daddy
     before we eat the cake.

46
00:04:44.312 --> 00:04:49.082
    Can't we even have an
    eensy-teensy little bite?
Yeah!

47
00:04:49.150 --> 00:04:52.119
    And give dad a cake
    that looks like a mouse
    has been nibbling at it?

48
00:04:52.186 --> 00:04:56.290
I've decided I'm gonna
do six rows of six.

49
00:04:56.357 --> 00:04:59.293
It's daddy!
        Cathy. dad's here!
        Come on out!

50
00:05:02.447 --> 00:05:04.448
    Get down.  Hurry.
     Get down here.

51
00:05:29.240 --> 00:05:32.293
    [ No Audible Dialogue ]

52
00:05:33.462 --> 00:05:36.630
            No-o-o-o!

53
00:05:48.259 --> 00:05:51.962
[ Narrating ]
When dad died.
Mother's grief overwhelmed her.

54
00:05:52.029 --> 00:05:55.332
We had to sell
everything we owned
just to survive.

55
00:05:55.400 --> 00:05:59.035
And when that money ran out.
they took our house.

56
00:05:59.371 --> 00:06:01.888
We were forced to leave
the place where we all grew up.

57
00:06:01.956 --> 00:06:05.192
where all our
happy memories were.

58
00:06:05.494 --> 00:06:07.845
the only home
I'd ever known.

59
00:06:07.912 --> 00:06:11.181
Mother said there was only
one place left to go.

60
00:06:19.174 --> 00:06:23.294
How come you never
took us to meet
the grandparents before?

61
00:06:23.361 --> 00:06:26.863
    I suppose because we were
    never penniless before.

62
00:06:26.932 --> 00:06:31.902
     <i>Years and years ago.</i>
     <i>I did something that</i>
     <i>angered your Grandfather.</i>

63
00:06:31.970 --> 00:06:34.805
             <i>His punishment was</i>
             <i>to disinherit me.</i>

64
00:06:34.872 --> 00:06:37.274
            Then why are we
            going there now?

65
00:06:37.342 --> 00:06:39.310
        If they won't give us
        any money?

66
00:06:39.377 --> 00:06:41.545
                Because he will.

67
00:06:41.612 --> 00:06:44.048
                Your Grandfather
                is dying.

68
00:06:44.115 --> 00:06:47.351
         <i>He's not expected</i>
         <i>to live much longer.</i>

69
00:06:47.419 --> 00:06:50.921
        But in that time.
        I'm going to win back
        his love.

70
00:06:52.657 --> 00:06:54.825
            And then. darlings.

71
00:06:54.892 --> 00:06:58.462
            I'll be the heiress
            to a fortune beyond
            your imaginations.

72
00:06:59.897 --> 00:07:04.001
    And through me.
    every dream you've ever had
    will come true.

73
00:07:09.707 --> 00:07:12.643
Mother should have prepared us
for something like this.

74
00:07:12.711 --> 00:07:14.645
What do you mean?

75
00:07:14.713 --> 00:07:19.149
    She never allowed us
    to have a dog or a kitten.

76
00:07:19.217 --> 00:07:22.219
What that's got to do
with anything?

77
00:07:22.286 --> 00:07:24.888
            Because pets die.
            Christopher.

78
00:07:24.956 --> 00:07:29.226
And if we had had a pet
and it had died. we would have
learned something about that.

79
00:07:29.293 --> 00:07:31.461
About what?
 About death?

80
00:07:31.529 --> 00:07:34.031
                Yes. death.
                Death.

81
00:07:34.099 --> 00:07:36.366
She should have told us.
Somebody should have told us...

82
00:07:36.434 --> 00:07:39.336
        that fathers die too.

83
00:07:39.403 --> 00:07:41.338
        They die. Christopher.

84
00:07:41.405 --> 00:07:45.743
        Even if they're young
        and they're handsome
        and we need them.

85
00:07:45.810 --> 00:07:47.945
        I don't want to be here.
        Christopher.

86
00:07:48.013 --> 00:07:50.781
    I don't want to go
    to the grandparents' house.

87
00:07:50.849 --> 00:07:53.017
            I could care less
            about being rich...

88
00:07:53.084 --> 00:07:56.353
            and having all
            my dreams come true.

89
00:07:56.420 --> 00:07:58.355
            All I want
            is to be at home...

90
00:07:58.422 --> 00:08:01.625
        and just stay at home
        where daddy's memory is.

91
00:08:08.933 --> 00:08:12.636
[ Cory ]
I don't want to walk at night.
It's scary.

92
00:08:12.704 --> 00:08:14.972
        [ Cathy ]
        Why didn't they send
        a car for us.

93
00:08:45.610 --> 00:08:50.045
[ Dogs Barking ]

94
00:09:33.635 --> 00:09:35.569
Witches in there. mama.

95
00:09:35.637 --> 00:09:38.071
Witches and monsters.

96
00:09:45.430 --> 00:09:47.597
            Good morning. John.

97
00:09:47.665 --> 00:09:50.134
                Children.
                this is John.

98
00:09:50.201 --> 00:09:52.269
        He's been with
        your grandparents for--

99
00:09:52.337 --> 00:09:54.871
            well. as long
            as I can remember.

100
00:09:54.940 --> 00:09:57.774
            This is Christopher
            and Cathy...

101
00:09:57.976 --> 00:10:00.311
and the twins.
Cory and Carrie.

102
00:10:00.378 --> 00:10:03.797
    Very nice
    to meet you. John.

103
00:10:42.503 --> 00:10:44.638
        Hello. Mother.

104
00:10:44.706 --> 00:10:47.874
    Leave all the bags
    with John. Corrine.

105
00:10:47.942 --> 00:10:50.444
    and bring the children
    upstairs.

106
00:12:31.095 --> 00:12:34.131
Let's get ready
for bed. children.

107
00:12:36.200 --> 00:12:39.303
Stay tonight. mama.

108
00:12:39.370 --> 00:12:41.771
    It's only 6:00
    in the morning.
    sweetheart.

109
00:12:41.839 --> 00:12:44.341
    Mama's got to take
    a little nap herself.

110
00:12:46.510 --> 00:12:48.445
    With us?

111
00:12:48.512 --> 00:12:52.916
        The boys will sleep
        in one bed. Corrine.
        the girls in the other.

112
00:12:52.984 --> 00:12:56.320
            But I want to sleep
            with Cory. mama.

113
00:12:56.387 --> 00:12:59.589
Stop your whimpering.
young lady. and listen to me.

114
00:12:59.657 --> 00:13:03.593
As long as you're in this house.
you will abide by my rules.

115
00:13:03.661 --> 00:13:05.878
         <i>You will not yell..</i>
         <i>or cry...</i>

116
00:13:05.946 --> 00:13:07.864
                or run about.

117
00:13:07.932 --> 00:13:12.802
    And when your Mother and I
    leave this room. we will
    lock this door behind us.

118
00:13:13.004 --> 00:13:16.306
Mother. please.
they're children.
You can't expect me to--

119
00:13:16.374 --> 00:13:18.308
                What I expect.
                Corrine.

120
00:13:18.376 --> 00:13:22.879
is that they will do
precisely as I've instructed.

121
00:13:24.882 --> 00:13:27.250
            Listen to mom.
            all of you.

122
00:13:27.318 --> 00:13:30.220
        Behave and obey
        your Grandmother...

123
00:13:30.288 --> 00:13:32.422
    and never ever give her
    any reason.

124
00:13:32.490 --> 00:13:34.858
        any reason at all.
        to punish you.

125
00:13:34.925 --> 00:13:38.462
        Please?
        Please do this.
        Make them obey.

126
00:13:38.529 --> 00:13:42.199
Make it seem like a game.
like a wonderful adventure.

127
00:13:42.266 --> 00:13:44.667
            Why are you crying.
            Mother?

128
00:13:46.104 --> 00:13:48.605
            I'll come back
            this afternoon.

129
00:13:51.976 --> 00:13:54.511
    [ Sobbing ]

130
00:13:59.049 --> 00:14:01.385
        Don't worry
        about us. mom.

131
00:14:01.452 --> 00:14:04.220
We'll be fine.

132
00:14:13.163 --> 00:14:15.932
                 <i>[ Door Locks ]</i>

133
00:14:18.369 --> 00:14:21.371
        It won't be so bad.
        That Grandmother--

134
00:14:21.439 --> 00:14:24.240
        she can't possibly be
        as mean as she seems.

135
00:16:10.731 --> 00:16:14.033
        Remember.
        God sees everything.

136
00:16:14.102 --> 00:16:17.704
        God will see
        whatever evil you do
        behind my back.

137
00:16:17.771 --> 00:16:20.207
        and he will punish you
        for it.

138
00:16:28.616 --> 00:16:30.933
     <i>Do you know why</i>
     <i>your Mother has come home?</i>

139
00:16:31.001 --> 00:16:33.336
Yes.  To win back
her Father's love....

140
00:16:33.404 --> 00:16:35.672
so he'll make her
part of his will again.

141
00:16:35.873 --> 00:16:39.359
    And why was she stricken
    from that will?
    Did she tell you that?

142
00:16:39.794 --> 00:16:43.079
        I have to go
        to the bathroom.

143
00:16:43.414 --> 00:16:45.499
        Be silent.

144
00:16:45.566 --> 00:16:47.501
        Learn control.

145
00:16:47.568 --> 00:16:51.471
    And never. never speak
    unless I ask you a question.

146
00:16:51.539 --> 00:16:55.142
                He's just
                a little boy--
        What did I just say?

147
00:16:57.378 --> 00:17:01.848
    Your Mother has come home
    after 17 years...

148
00:17:01.916 --> 00:17:05.318
    to repent for her sins
    and for her crimes--

149
00:17:05.386 --> 00:17:08.621
    not only against
    your Grandfather and me...

150
00:17:08.689 --> 00:17:10.957
            but against God.

151
00:17:11.025 --> 00:17:14.944
         <i>Your Mother's marriage</i>
         <i>was unholy.</i>

152
00:17:15.012 --> 00:17:17.113
                 <i>a sacrilege.</i>

153
00:17:17.181 --> 00:17:20.783
     <i>an abomination</i>
     <i>in the eyes of the lord.</i>

154
00:17:20.851 --> 00:17:24.887
    She did not fall from grace.
     She leapt...

155
00:17:24.955 --> 00:17:28.024
         <i>into the arms of a man</i>
         <i>whose veins...</i>

156
00:17:28.092 --> 00:17:30.393
         <i>pulsed with the same</i>
         <i>blood as hers.</i>

157
00:17:30.461 --> 00:17:33.229
            Not a stranger.

158
00:17:33.297 --> 00:17:35.498
        but her own uncle.

159
00:17:35.566 --> 00:17:38.368
                 <i>And you.</i>
                 <i>the children.</i>

160
00:17:38.436 --> 00:17:40.370
         <i>are the devil's spawn.</i>

161
00:17:40.438 --> 00:17:43.706
        Evil from the moment
        of conception.

162
00:17:43.774 --> 00:17:45.909
    I'm getting
    my Mother!
            Come back here!

163
00:17:45.976 --> 00:17:48.445
                    [ Screams ]
                 <i>Come back here.</i>

164
00:17:51.232 --> 00:17:53.233
                    Sit down.

165
00:17:54.969 --> 00:17:57.838
            And don't move again
            until I leave.

166
00:17:59.240 --> 00:18:01.374
             <i>There is</i>
             <i>one other matter.</i>

167
00:18:01.442 --> 00:18:05.094
    Your Grandfather will not
    be told that you are here.

168
00:18:05.162 --> 00:18:07.697
        He will never be told.

169
00:18:07.765 --> 00:18:11.534
        He has no idea
        that you even exist--
        any of you.

170
00:18:11.602 --> 00:18:15.805
             <i>No idea that you</i>
             <i>were ever born.</i>

171
00:18:15.873 --> 00:18:18.708
    As long as he lives--
    and I swear this to you--

172
00:18:18.776 --> 00:18:22.579
        I will spare him that
        final agony of shame.

173
00:18:30.121 --> 00:18:33.106
             <i>[ Door Locking ]</i>
<i>I don't like it</i>
<i>here. Cathy.</i>

174
00:18:33.174 --> 00:18:35.876
I wanna go home.

175
00:19:26.593 --> 00:19:29.462
[ Whip Cracks ]

176
00:19:57.257 --> 00:19:59.693
[ Door Unlocking ]

177
00:19:59.760 --> 00:20:02.562
Mama!

178
00:20:02.630 --> 00:20:05.598
Where have you been. mama?
 Where have you been?

179
00:20:05.666 --> 00:20:09.536
    [ Children Chattering ]

180
00:20:09.603 --> 00:20:13.973
    Oh. mama's here.
    Mama's here.
    Mama's here.

181
00:20:14.041 --> 00:20:16.543
What's wrong. mom?
What happened to you?

182
00:20:16.610 --> 00:20:20.380
     <i>Corrine!</i>
     <i>You will stop those</i>
     <i>children's screaming...</i>

183
00:20:20.448 --> 00:20:22.849
        this very moment!

184
00:20:33.627 --> 00:20:36.529
                [ Screaming ]

185
00:20:39.416 --> 00:20:42.919
    - No!  Devil!
    - [ Screaming Continues ]

186
00:20:45.006 --> 00:20:47.507
Mama. make her stop!

187
00:20:47.574 --> 00:20:49.125
    Corrine.
    control your children...

188
00:20:49.192 --> 00:20:52.161
        or I'll whip them
        till the blood runs
        from their backs!

189
00:20:52.229 --> 00:20:54.396
         <i>Your children are</i>
         <i>spoiled and indulged...</i>

190
00:20:54.464 --> 00:20:56.499
             <i>and need lessons</i>
             <i>in obedience.</i>

191
00:20:56.566 --> 00:20:59.168
        No child that lives
        under this roof...

192
00:20:59.236 --> 00:21:01.671
                 <i>will disobey...</i>

193
00:21:01.739 --> 00:21:04.107
             <i>or scream.</i>
            <i>or show defiance.</i>

194
00:21:04.174 --> 00:21:06.442
            Do you hear me?

195
00:21:06.510 --> 00:21:09.411
                Do you?

196
00:21:11.181 --> 00:21:14.617
        Now. remove
        your blouse. daughter.

197
00:21:15.853 --> 00:21:19.155
    and show them how punishment
    is given in this house.

198
00:21:19.222 --> 00:21:22.525
    If you're cruel
    to my children.
    I'll take them away tonight.

199
00:21:22.592 --> 00:21:25.094
        Take them. Corrine.

200
00:21:25.162 --> 00:21:28.698
    Take them now!
    Do you think I care?

201
00:21:28.766 --> 00:21:31.200
                    [ Laughing ]

202
00:21:34.071 --> 00:21:36.372
            Take off the blouse.
            Corrine.

203
00:21:39.043 --> 00:21:41.243
                    Take it off.

204
00:21:46.884 --> 00:21:49.385
             <i>Now. look closely.</i>
             <i>children.</i>

205
00:21:49.720 --> 00:21:52.472
             <i>Seventeen lashes.</i>

206
00:21:52.540 --> 00:21:56.843
             <i>One for each year</i>
             <i>she lived in sin</i>
             <i>with your Father.</i>

207
00:21:56.911 --> 00:21:59.646
             <i>So that you</i>
             <i>understand me now.</i>

208
00:21:59.713 --> 00:22:02.916
            I will give you
            food and shelter.

209
00:22:02.983 --> 00:22:06.319
            but never kindness
            or love.

210
00:22:06.386 --> 00:22:10.523
    For it is impossible to feel
    anything but disgust...

211
00:22:10.591 --> 00:22:13.225
            for what is not
            wholesome.

212
00:22:37.968 --> 00:22:39.902
        It's better.

213
00:22:39.970 --> 00:22:43.639
If I had some antiseptic--
        [ Chuckles ]
        My young doctor.

214
00:22:45.542 --> 00:22:47.910
    The years of happiness
    I had with your Father...

215
00:22:47.978 --> 00:22:50.346
        are worth
        a hundred whippings.

216
00:22:50.414 --> 00:22:53.182
    The things that Grandmother
    said to us. Mother.

217
00:22:53.250 --> 00:22:55.485
                    they are
                    ugly things.

218
00:22:55.552 --> 00:22:57.620
They hurt you. mom.

219
00:22:57.688 --> 00:22:59.622
I hate them
for that.

220
00:22:59.690 --> 00:23:01.891
    The worst is over.

221
00:23:01.958 --> 00:23:03.893
    Beginning tomorrow.

222
00:23:03.960 --> 00:23:07.263
    I'm going to start to
    win back my Father's love.

223
00:23:07.330 --> 00:23:10.633
    If you help me.
     if all of you help me--

224
00:23:10.701 --> 00:23:13.636
        by doing what I ask.
         by being good--

225
00:23:13.704 --> 00:23:15.705
        I'll succeed.

226
00:23:25.382 --> 00:23:27.950
[ Whispering. Indistinct ]

227
00:23:43.550 --> 00:23:47.420
        The closet on the right
        has a secret panel.

228
00:23:47.487 --> 00:23:50.456
Look for it tomorrow morning.
If you push on it gently.
it'll open.

229
00:23:50.524 --> 00:23:52.826
            You'll see
            a narrow stairway.

230
00:23:52.893 --> 00:23:56.830
            Up the stairs
            is an attic.
            an attic so big...

231
00:23:56.897 --> 00:23:59.298
                you could easily
                get lost in it.

232
00:23:59.366 --> 00:24:02.535
            Make it a playground
            for the twins.
            Make it--

233
00:24:02.603 --> 00:24:04.938
                 <i>Make it your</i>
                 <i>special place.</i>

234
00:24:15.415 --> 00:24:17.516
                 <i>[ Door Locks ]</i>

235
00:24:21.455 --> 00:24:23.990
Do you need
to use the bathroom?

236
00:24:24.058 --> 00:24:26.059
                            No.

237
00:24:27.361 --> 00:24:29.662
Not even to
brush your teeth?

238
00:24:30.798 --> 00:24:33.133
            I don't feel like it
            tonight.

239
00:24:50.700 --> 00:24:53.669
        What do you think about
        all that talk?

240
00:24:53.737 --> 00:24:56.105
        Uncles marrying nieces?

241
00:24:56.173 --> 00:24:59.008
        Maybe having kids
        with thorns and tails?

242
00:24:59.076 --> 00:25:01.544
You're the future doctor.

243
00:25:01.611 --> 00:25:03.812
What do you think?
Could it really happen?

244
00:25:03.880 --> 00:25:06.432
            You sure can't
            prove it by us.

245
00:25:09.536 --> 00:25:12.722
    - What are you thinking?
    - About mom.

246
00:25:14.257 --> 00:25:17.393
How different she's become
since daddy died.

247
00:25:17.728 --> 00:25:21.513
    She hasn't been different.
    Just sad.

248
00:25:21.949 --> 00:25:24.300
    We're sad. too. Christopher.

249
00:25:24.368 --> 00:25:27.103
    It hasn't changed
    who we are.

250
00:25:56.567 --> 00:25:59.302
        What if
        the Grandmother comes in
        before we wake up...

251
00:25:59.369 --> 00:26:01.770
                and sees us in
                the same bed?

252
00:26:01.838 --> 00:26:05.774
Then we'll sic Cory on her.
He can bite her other leg.

253
00:26:05.842 --> 00:26:07.776
        She doesn't scare you?

254
00:26:07.844 --> 00:26:10.546
    Nobody scares me.

255
00:26:10.614 --> 00:26:13.516
Anyway. we used to sleep
in the same bed all the time.

256
00:26:17.221 --> 00:26:19.622
            [ Sighs ]

257
00:26:52.422 --> 00:26:54.356
        I've listed the rules
        you're to follow...

258
00:26:54.424 --> 00:26:56.558
            as long as you live
            in my house.

259
00:26:56.626 --> 00:27:00.963
Read them carefully
and put them to memory.

260
00:27:17.847 --> 00:27:20.516
Grab some food.
We don't want to starve
up there.

261
00:27:21.818 --> 00:27:23.952
            Let's go find
            those stairs.

262
00:27:37.367 --> 00:27:40.503
        I found it.
            What do you see.
            Christopher?

263
00:27:41.538 --> 00:27:44.557
    Nothing to see
    from here.

264
00:27:44.624 --> 00:27:47.126
    Just some stairs.

265
00:27:48.979 --> 00:27:50.947
            Is everybody ready
            to go up?

266
00:27:51.014 --> 00:27:52.949
[ Door Opens ]
[ Grandmother ]
Not yet.

267
00:27:53.016 --> 00:27:56.886
    Your Mother was given
    permission to tell you
    about the attic.

268
00:27:57.354 --> 00:27:59.472
             <i>But let me</i>
             <i>remind you again.</i>

269
00:27:59.539 --> 00:28:01.707
    You must never be seen.

270
00:28:39.546 --> 00:28:41.547
            My God.

271
00:29:33.934 --> 00:29:36.069
[ Narrating ]
Grandmother's rules
weren't rules.

272
00:29:36.136 --> 00:29:38.171
they were cruel punishments.

273
00:29:38.238 --> 00:29:41.574
We were trapped.
and the only way we could
even feel the sunlight...

274
00:29:41.641 --> 00:29:44.677
was to look out
a barred window.

275
00:29:44.744 --> 00:29:47.880
Our Mother must've been
desperate to have come back.

276
00:29:47.948 --> 00:29:50.683
We were all going to
pay the price.

277
00:30:04.381 --> 00:30:06.582
                 <i>♪ [ Piano ]</i>

278
00:31:15.419 --> 00:31:17.620
[ Narrating ]
As the weeks became months.

279
00:31:17.687 --> 00:31:20.456
our memories of our real home
began to fade.

280
00:31:20.524 --> 00:31:23.625
But we clung to our dreams.

281
00:31:23.693 --> 00:31:26.529
Chris wanted to go
to medical school someday.

282
00:31:26.596 --> 00:31:29.598
and I wanted to be
a dancer.

283
00:31:29.666 --> 00:31:31.900
We tried to act
like a family.

284
00:31:31.968 --> 00:31:34.903
It was the only way
we could survive.

285
00:31:54.007 --> 00:31:56.709
Mother's visits became
fewer and fewer.

286
00:31:56.776 --> 00:31:59.745
and then stopped altogether.

287
00:31:59.813 --> 00:32:03.316
We imagined that something
horrible had happened to her.

288
00:32:03.383 --> 00:32:05.951
Or had we been forgotten?

289
00:32:06.019 --> 00:32:08.454
There seemed to be
no way to escape.

290
00:32:08.522 --> 00:32:11.156
but soon. very soon.

291
00:32:11.225 --> 00:32:13.392
we'd have to find a way
past Grandmother...

292
00:32:13.460 --> 00:32:18.097
to find and to help Mother
if we could.

293
00:32:18.265 --> 00:32:20.816
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

294
00:32:26.389 --> 00:32:28.857
Do you think
it's a good snail?

295
00:32:28.925 --> 00:32:32.261
        I think
        it's a wonderful snail.
        It's very beautiful.

296
00:32:32.329 --> 00:32:35.964
It doesn't look
like an orange?

297
00:32:36.032 --> 00:32:38.467
        Not in the very least.

298
00:32:38.535 --> 00:32:41.570
        And I've never seen
        an orange with feelers.
        Have you?

299
00:32:41.638 --> 00:32:45.307
             <i>[ Christopher ]</i>
             <i>Antennae. Cathy.</i>
             <i>Not feelers.</i>

300
00:32:45.375 --> 00:32:48.544
     <i>Snails are members</i>
     <i>of the family of Mollusks--</i>

301
00:32:48.612 --> 00:32:51.013
                 <i>Soft bodies.</i>
                 <i>no backbones.</i>

302
00:32:51.080 --> 00:32:54.383
     <i>And tubular intestines</i>
     <i>that end with their mouths.</i>

303
00:32:54.451 --> 00:32:57.153
    Dear Dr. Christopher.
    When Cory and I want
    to hear...

304
00:32:57.220 --> 00:33:00.189
    about a snail's guts.
    then we will...
[ Chuckles ]

305
00:33:00.257 --> 00:33:03.759
    send you a telegram
    or something. thank you.

306
00:33:03.826 --> 00:33:06.795
                When do we get
                to go outside?

307
00:33:06.863 --> 00:33:08.797
                As soon as mom
                says we can.

308
00:33:08.865 --> 00:33:11.200
But mama doesn't
come anymore.

309
00:33:11.268 --> 00:33:15.003
        If we could go outside.
        we'd have real flowers
        and real grass.

310
00:33:15.071 --> 00:33:17.206
And real snails.

311
00:33:18.074 --> 00:33:20.475
        God's taken
        all the grass to heaven.

312
00:33:20.544 --> 00:33:23.145
Why?
                For daddy.

313
00:33:23.212 --> 00:33:26.081
    Remember how he used to mow
    the lawn all the time?

314
00:33:26.149 --> 00:33:29.318
        Why do we have to stay
        upstairs all the time?

315
00:33:29.386 --> 00:33:33.556
'Cause downstairs
has gone away.
    That's not true. Cory.

316
00:33:33.623 --> 00:33:35.891
            Mama doesn't like us
            anymore.

317
00:33:35.958 --> 00:33:38.960
    Stop it. you two.
I itch.

318
00:33:39.028 --> 00:33:41.096
            Mama's being mean.
            We want a TV.

319
00:33:41.164 --> 00:33:44.266
        We want our ice cream.
        We want to play
        with our friends.

320
00:33:44.334 --> 00:33:46.268
                We want to go
                outside.

321
00:33:46.336 --> 00:33:48.804
Don't you want to go to school?
No!
                        No!

322
00:33:48.871 --> 00:33:52.974
        Look at me.
         Look at me. all of you.

323
00:33:53.042 --> 00:33:56.278
        The bible says there's
        a time for everything.

324
00:33:56.346 --> 00:33:58.280
            A time to be born.

325
00:33:58.748 --> 00:34:00.533
             <i>A time to plant.</i>

326
00:34:00.600 --> 00:34:02.635
             <i>A time to harvest.</i>

327
00:34:02.703 --> 00:34:06.138
Probably a time
to have ice cream too.

328
00:34:06.206 --> 00:34:09.241
                This is our time
                to sacrifice.

329
00:34:09.309 --> 00:34:11.711
                    For mom.

330
00:34:11.778 --> 00:34:13.813
            Later on. we'll have
            plenty of time...

331
00:34:13.880 --> 00:34:16.816
            to live and enjoy.

332
00:34:30.814 --> 00:34:32.782
        [ Knocking ]
    Cathy?

333
00:34:32.849 --> 00:34:35.651
Can I come in?

334
00:34:35.718 --> 00:34:38.487
    Close the door
    so we won't wake the twins.

335
00:34:51.017 --> 00:34:54.686
Something could've
happened to mom.

336
00:34:54.754 --> 00:34:56.755
Maybe she's sick.

337
00:34:56.822 --> 00:34:59.724
        Mom's always been
        healthy as a horse.

338
00:34:59.792 --> 00:35:02.428
Well. where's she been
all this time?

339
00:35:02.495 --> 00:35:04.963
Why'd she stop
coming to see us?

340
00:35:08.601 --> 00:35:10.969
And I had
another thought.

341
00:35:11.037 --> 00:35:12.971
A terrible thought.

342
00:35:13.039 --> 00:35:14.973
                What?

343
00:35:15.041 --> 00:35:18.710
What if they've
locked her up somewhere
in this huge house?

344
00:35:18.778 --> 00:35:21.313
Just like
they've locked us up.

345
00:35:21.381 --> 00:35:23.415
        Why would they want
        to do that?

346
00:35:23.483 --> 00:35:25.984
To punish her.
Why do you think?

347
00:35:26.052 --> 00:35:29.621
'Cause they're crazy
as loons.

348
00:35:29.689 --> 00:35:31.957
            Gave me a chill.

349
00:35:32.024 --> 00:35:35.026
Giving myself chills
just thinking about it.

350
00:35:37.564 --> 00:35:40.065
            I'm sure
            it's not true.

351
00:35:40.133 --> 00:35:42.568
How can you be sure?

352
00:35:44.404 --> 00:35:46.338
                Does it matter?

353
00:35:46.406 --> 00:35:49.575
        We're never gonna know
        until she comes
        to see us again.

354
00:35:50.943 --> 00:35:52.944
    Oh. yeah?

355
00:35:55.215 --> 00:35:58.016
            What's that
            supposed to mean?
I've got a plan.

356
00:35:58.084 --> 00:36:00.685
        Christopher. what are
        you thinking of doing?

357
00:36:00.753 --> 00:36:03.555
Don't worry about it.
                Christopher!

358
00:36:03.623 --> 00:36:06.958
Shh.  You don't want
to wake the twins.

359
00:36:10.997 --> 00:36:13.832
            Carrie. you're
            in the wrong bed.

360
00:36:16.136 --> 00:36:19.337
    I want to sleep
    with Cory tonight.

361
00:36:42.462 --> 00:36:44.530
[ Unlocking ]

362
00:36:51.922 --> 00:36:54.790
    Get up!
     Get out of those beds!

363
00:37:21.151 --> 00:37:24.336
    Don't!  Don't touch that!
    No-o-o!

364
00:37:24.404 --> 00:37:27.539
            My Father gave that
            to me!

365
00:37:27.707 --> 00:37:30.325
            Oh. God!
            [ Sobbing ]

366
00:37:36.066 --> 00:37:38.467
            No-o-o!

367
00:37:51.964 --> 00:37:53.899
        Tell me. Christopher.

368
00:37:53.966 --> 00:37:56.201
    You thought of a way
    out of here. haven't you?

369
00:37:56.269 --> 00:37:59.538
        Without the Grandfather
        finding out.

370
00:37:59.606 --> 00:38:02.541
I've thought about it
for weeks. Cathy.

371
00:38:02.609 --> 00:38:05.277
It's the only thing
I've <i>been</i> thinking about.

372
00:38:05.344 --> 00:38:07.479
                Can it be done?

373
00:38:09.181 --> 00:38:12.083
            Christopher.
            if Mother's here.
            we have to find her.

374
00:38:12.151 --> 00:38:14.453
        We've got to tell her.

375
00:38:15.855 --> 00:38:18.791
    We will.
    Tonight.

376
00:38:42.582 --> 00:38:45.150
[ Christopher ]
Okay. grab the bar. Cathy.

377
00:38:45.218 --> 00:38:49.388
            [ Grunting ]

378
00:38:49.456 --> 00:38:51.790
            Okay. pull it.

379
00:38:54.294 --> 00:38:57.862
            Come on. pull!
            Yeah.

380
00:38:57.930 --> 00:39:00.099
                That's it.
                Grab it.

381
00:39:00.166 --> 00:39:02.568
[ Grunting ]
                Pull.
                 Pull. Cathy.

382
00:39:30.847 --> 00:39:33.147
[ Thunder Crashing ]

383
00:39:34.684 --> 00:39:36.718
I'm going with you.

384
00:39:36.786 --> 00:39:38.987
                No chance.
    Yes!

385
00:39:41.491 --> 00:39:44.459
                All right.
                But I go first.

386
00:39:44.527 --> 00:39:48.263
        And you don't lay one
        hand on this rope till
        I get all the way down.

387
00:39:48.330 --> 00:39:51.633
                You understand?
I understand.

388
00:40:00.493 --> 00:40:02.561
Be careful.

389
00:40:18.294 --> 00:40:20.963
    Careful!
            Oh!

390
00:41:27.814 --> 00:41:29.331
            What?

391
00:41:31.167 --> 00:41:33.435
        [ Barking ]
[ Christopher ]
My God.

392
00:41:34.803 --> 00:41:37.506
        Get out of here!
        Quick!

393
00:42:25.938 --> 00:42:29.207
    Come on!
     Come on!

394
00:42:31.110 --> 00:42:34.045
[ Barking Continues ]

395
00:42:37.467 --> 00:42:39.751
    Come on!

396
00:42:42.938 --> 00:42:45.440
    [ Screaming ]

397
00:42:49.979 --> 00:42:51.747
        Christopher!

398
00:42:51.814 --> 00:42:54.783
            Cathy!
Christopher!

399
00:42:58.821 --> 00:43:01.390
Come on. Christopher!

400
00:43:08.497 --> 00:43:11.166
Come on!
Throw the rope!
I can catch it!

401
00:43:29.518 --> 00:43:32.988
Christopher. you can make it!
Just climb!

402
00:43:35.024 --> 00:43:38.360
Come on. Christopher!

403
00:43:43.232 --> 00:43:45.233
            Ah!

404
00:44:19.001 --> 00:44:21.236
             <i>[ Door Unlocking ]</i>

405
00:44:24.140 --> 00:44:26.908
        Mama?
                         <i>Shh.</i>

406
00:44:30.612 --> 00:44:32.613
    Mama?

407
00:44:35.918 --> 00:44:37.768
Mama!  Mama!
 Mama!

408
00:44:37.836 --> 00:44:39.971
                    Oh!

409
00:44:40.038 --> 00:44:42.707
Christopher made me
a swing. mama.

410
00:44:42.774 --> 00:44:44.842
        And we made a garden
        of paper flowers.

411
00:44:45.144 --> 00:44:49.364
Here!
And Cathy has them pasted
up right near the window!

412
00:44:49.431 --> 00:44:52.300
You've been wonderful with them.
Look how happy they are.

413
00:44:52.368 --> 00:44:55.737
    Happy to see you. mama.
    but not happy to be here.

414
00:45:04.380 --> 00:45:07.014
You haven't been to see us
in so long. mom.

415
00:45:07.082 --> 00:45:09.150
We were worried
about you.

416
00:45:09.218 --> 00:45:11.386
        Is that why you tried
        to run away?

417
00:45:11.454 --> 00:45:14.289
                    Is it?
                    Answer me.

418
00:45:14.357 --> 00:45:17.525
We weren't trying
to run away. Mother.
We were trying to find you.

419
00:45:17.593 --> 00:45:21.896
    Didn't it occur to you
    you could've ruin my plan?
    Our plan?

420
00:45:21.964 --> 00:45:24.733
Don't you understand?
I told you.

421
00:45:24.800 --> 00:45:26.901
My Father--
            The twins aren't
            healthy. Mother.

422
00:45:26.969 --> 00:45:29.604
        They need to be outside
        in the fresh air
        and the sun.

423
00:45:29.672 --> 00:45:31.740
            They need to be
            with their friends.

424
00:45:31.807 --> 00:45:35.143
        They need plenty of room
        to run around. and they
        need to be in school.

425
00:45:36.245 --> 00:45:39.947
        All right.
        I'll leave it up to you.

426
00:45:40.015 --> 00:45:43.518
        We can pack our things
        and leave today--
                Yes!

427
00:45:43.586 --> 00:45:47.689
Or we can wait a little longer
until the reading of the will.

428
00:45:49.158 --> 00:45:51.559
    Grandfather's dying?

429
00:45:51.627 --> 00:45:53.995
The doctors say
he won't live out the month.

430
00:45:57.266 --> 00:45:59.200
If we leave now.
we have nothing.

431
00:45:59.268 --> 00:46:01.202
        Nowhere to go.

432
00:46:01.270 --> 00:46:06.608
    If we stay. we-- we'll have
    more than we could
    ever want-- forever.

433
00:46:06.676 --> 00:46:09.110
        We love you. mom.

434
00:46:10.212 --> 00:46:12.180
        Whatever
        you think's best.

435
00:46:12.247 --> 00:46:15.283
That's what we'll do.

436
00:46:15.351 --> 00:46:18.787
        Cathy. you have a say
        in this too.

437
00:46:22.057 --> 00:46:24.892
            I think I'd better
            check on the twins.

438
00:46:28.431 --> 00:46:30.765
We'll be all right.
mom.

439
00:46:30.833 --> 00:46:33.168
If it's just
a little longer.

440
00:46:33.235 --> 00:46:35.603
we'll be all right.

441
00:46:35.671 --> 00:46:37.672
    Don't worry.

442
00:47:00.113 --> 00:47:02.414
I've got him!
I got him!

443
00:47:02.482 --> 00:47:05.650
Christopher!
I've got a pet!

444
00:47:05.718 --> 00:47:09.554
"I hate vain thoughts.
 but thy law do I love.

445
00:47:09.622 --> 00:47:13.191
Thou art my hiding place
and my shield."

446
00:47:39.167 --> 00:47:42.437
Christopher.
come and look
what happened.

447
00:47:47.843 --> 00:47:50.512
Why did you put up
more bars?

448
00:48:27.849 --> 00:48:31.619
[ Narrating ]  I knew Chris
would have second thoughts
about agreeing with Mother.

449
00:48:31.687 --> 00:48:34.355
I found a way to escape.
even if it was only...

450
00:48:34.423 --> 00:48:37.091
to a hot bath
and my fantasies--

451
00:48:37.159 --> 00:48:39.494
Fantasies of a life
filled with dancing.

452
00:48:39.561 --> 00:48:42.930
friends.
and maybe even romance.

453
00:48:42.998 --> 00:48:45.500
Fantasies that might
never come true.

454
00:48:50.839 --> 00:48:53.124
[ Knocking ]

455
00:48:53.192 --> 00:48:55.560
    Cathy?
                    Yes?

456
00:48:56.828 --> 00:48:59.497
    - Can I come in and talk?
    - What is it?

457
00:48:59.565 --> 00:49:02.633
You're not mad at me
for siding with mom. are you?

458
00:49:02.701 --> 00:49:06.137
No. but why do you always
have to agree with her?

459
00:49:06.205 --> 00:49:08.489
                    Sinners!

460
00:49:09.491 --> 00:49:12.126
Christopher!

461
00:49:12.461 --> 00:49:14.145
What have we done
to be called sinners?

462
00:49:14.213 --> 00:49:18.149
Do you expect us to live
in one room. week after week.
and not see each other?

463
00:49:18.217 --> 00:49:21.652
You put us here.
You-you locked us in.

464
00:49:21.721 --> 00:49:25.590
You want to catch us
doing something
you can call evil.

465
00:49:25.657 --> 00:49:27.592
Look at you
in your black dress...

466
00:49:27.659 --> 00:49:30.528
and your fancy jewels
 and your pinched face.

467
00:49:30.596 --> 00:49:33.064
We're not afraid of you.
We laugh at you.

468
00:49:33.132 --> 00:49:36.735
Do you hear that?  We laugh.
Get out!  Out!
                [ Locks Door ]

469
00:49:49.048 --> 00:49:51.750
    Mom won't let her do
    anything to hurt us. Cathy.

470
00:49:53.869 --> 00:49:55.987
        We have to barricade
        the door.

471
00:49:56.055 --> 00:49:58.089
    or we'll hide in the attic.

472
00:49:58.157 --> 00:50:00.091
        She won't come up there.

473
00:50:00.159 --> 00:50:04.062
    I'm so scared. Christopher.

474
00:50:05.464 --> 00:50:07.632
            We'll be all right.

475
00:50:07.699 --> 00:50:09.868
    Mom'll make sure of that.

476
00:50:10.936 --> 00:50:12.937
                So will I.

477
00:51:04.172 --> 00:51:06.173
        Cory?

478
00:51:11.914 --> 00:51:14.849
    What is it?
    What's wrong?
                Cory's gone.

479
00:51:16.151 --> 00:51:18.385
            Cory?

480
00:51:22.925 --> 00:51:25.960
         <i>[ Cathy ]</i>
         <i>Cory!  Where are you?</i>
    <i>Cory!  Cory!</i>

481
00:51:26.027 --> 00:51:28.195
                Cory!
                    Cory!

482
00:51:28.263 --> 00:51:31.231
Fred's gone.
Look. you guys go that way.

483
00:51:31.299 --> 00:51:34.401
Cory!
Cory!              Cory!

484
00:51:34.470 --> 00:51:37.071
Cory!  Cory!
         <i>Cory!  Cory!</i>

485
00:51:37.138 --> 00:51:39.073
                         <i>Cory?</i>

486
00:51:39.140 --> 00:51:41.108
    Cory!
                     <i>Cory!</i>

487
00:51:41.176 --> 00:51:44.979
            Cory?
            He's here.

488
00:51:51.052 --> 00:51:53.304
Cory!
 Cory. wake up!

489
00:51:53.372 --> 00:51:55.873
Wake up. honey!
Come on!

490
00:51:55.941 --> 00:51:57.875
            Fred got out.

491
00:51:57.943 --> 00:52:00.645
        I had to catch him
        again.

492
00:52:00.713 --> 00:52:04.515
            Where is Fred?
        He's right here.

493
00:52:05.684 --> 00:52:08.653
        Guess we'd better keep
        Fred downstairs. huh?

494
00:52:09.921 --> 00:52:11.922
    Ohh.

495
00:52:25.621 --> 00:52:27.805
            Cathy!

496
00:52:27.873 --> 00:52:31.442
    Cathy.  Cathy!
    Open the door!

497
00:52:35.497 --> 00:52:38.265
Cathy!  Come on.
Open the door.

498
00:52:38.333 --> 00:52:41.335
Cathy!
 Cathy!
[ Pounding on Door ]

499
00:52:41.403 --> 00:52:44.138
            You are a sinner.
Open the door!

500
00:52:44.205 --> 00:52:48.342
Come on. open the door!
What's going on?
Cathy!

501
00:52:48.544 --> 00:52:52.397
Cathy!
 Cathy!
[ Pounding Continues ]

502
00:52:54.866 --> 00:52:56.867
                [ Door Unlocks ]

503
00:53:33.154 --> 00:53:35.222
                     <i>[ Sobbing ]</i>

504
00:53:42.798 --> 00:53:46.601
[ Cathy ]
Why is Mother
doing this to us?

505
00:53:51.190 --> 00:53:53.291
Mom doesn't know
what happened.

506
00:53:53.359 --> 00:53:55.393
I'm sure of it.

507
00:53:55.461 --> 00:53:58.496
    Why doesn't she come back?

508
00:53:58.563 --> 00:54:01.099
She'll come. Cathy.

509
00:54:01.166 --> 00:54:03.101
    Soon.

510
00:54:03.168 --> 00:54:05.169
You'll see.

511
00:54:42.541 --> 00:54:46.544
    Why didn't the Grandmother
    bring our food today?

512
00:54:46.612 --> 00:54:48.863
She's just coming late.
that's all.

513
00:54:49.197 --> 00:54:51.682
                Maybe there is
                no more food.

514
00:54:51.750 --> 00:54:54.184
            Maybe they ran out.

515
00:54:54.252 --> 00:54:57.838
    I'm not hungry anyway.

516
00:54:58.891 --> 00:55:00.892
She'll be here.

517
00:55:11.437 --> 00:55:13.771
        Oh!

518
00:55:15.841 --> 00:55:18.709
        Oh!

519
00:55:18.777 --> 00:55:20.812
        [ Giggles ]

520
00:55:29.671 --> 00:55:32.373
Good evening.
    Good evening.
    Mr. Winslow.

521
00:55:40.148 --> 00:55:43.417
[ Narrating ]
Starved for both
sunlight and food.

522
00:55:43.485 --> 00:55:47.588
our faces became pale
and our bodies thin.

523
00:55:47.656 --> 00:55:49.957
When Grandmother stopped
feeding us.

524
00:55:50.024 --> 00:55:52.526
little Cory became
very sick.

525
00:55:52.594 --> 00:55:56.430
and every day. we watched him
become weaker and weaker.

526
00:56:30.165 --> 00:56:32.299
                Move him over.

527
00:56:41.243 --> 00:56:43.477
What are you doing?

528
00:56:46.281 --> 00:56:49.049
What are you doing?
            Hold his head up.

529
00:56:50.152 --> 00:56:52.319
Why?
What are you gonna do?

530
00:56:52.387 --> 00:56:54.588
            Just do what I say.

531
00:57:02.397 --> 00:57:04.531
                I figured
                another way out.

532
00:57:04.599 --> 00:57:06.901
                I'm gonna try it
                tonight.

533
00:57:09.037 --> 00:57:12.106
    If you want to go with me.
    all the better.

534
00:57:12.174 --> 00:57:15.309
            If not.
            I'll go by myself.

535
00:58:29.250 --> 00:58:31.318
            Check that door.

536
00:59:39.771 --> 00:59:42.039
            Cathy--

537
00:59:48.446 --> 00:59:51.182
It's Mother's.

538
00:59:52.818 --> 00:59:55.452
        This is Mother's room.

539
01:00:08.867 --> 01:00:12.469
        [ Sobs ]
            Come on.
            We can't stay here.

540
01:00:12.537 --> 01:00:15.039
        Look.
        there's an explanation
        for all this. Cathy.

541
01:00:15.107 --> 01:00:17.507
        As soon as we find mom.
        we'll ask.
[ Exhales ]

542
01:00:17.575 --> 01:00:20.277
            And she'll tell us.

543
01:00:20.345 --> 01:00:23.047
    Come on.
    We've gotta keep looking.

544
01:00:34.359 --> 01:00:36.427
Let's go that way.

545
01:01:44.195 --> 01:01:46.196
            It's him.

546
01:01:46.264 --> 01:01:49.399
He's dead.
Christopher.

547
01:01:49.467 --> 01:01:53.737
What if he sees us?
        How can he see us
        if he's dead?

548
01:02:33.511 --> 01:02:36.746
[ Screaming ]

549
01:02:37.182 --> 01:02:40.434
    I always thought
    you were the best. Corrine.

550
01:02:46.007 --> 01:02:48.074
[ Screams ]

551
01:02:58.386 --> 01:03:00.454
    Here!

552
01:03:44.633 --> 01:03:46.967
        Do you love her
        as much as you used to?

553
01:03:47.035 --> 01:03:50.704
Don't ask stupid questions.

554
01:03:50.772 --> 01:03:55.108
Wherever she is tonight.
she's thinkin' of us...

555
01:03:55.176 --> 01:03:57.177
and she'll be comin' back.

556
01:03:57.245 --> 01:03:59.312
And when she does
this will all make sense.

557
01:03:59.380 --> 01:04:02.550
            The twins are sick.
            Christopher.
They'll be all right.

558
01:04:02.617 --> 01:04:05.586
                    Chris!
No!  I don't want
to talk about it anymore.

559
01:04:05.654 --> 01:04:10.490
That crazy. sick old man is not
gonna live forever. Cathy.

560
01:04:10.559 --> 01:04:12.560
    You could see that tonight.

561
01:04:12.627 --> 01:04:16.463
        He didn't even know
        who we were.
        Who <i>you</i> were.

562
01:04:16.531 --> 01:04:20.034
Did you forget
why we came here
in the first place?

563
01:04:20.101 --> 01:04:24.071
    All the money in the world
    isn't worth the living
    that we've lost.

564
01:04:24.138 --> 01:04:26.022
    Well. maybe not for you.

565
01:04:26.090 --> 01:04:28.358
    but without some of it.
    mom doesn't have a thing.

566
01:04:28.426 --> 01:04:31.027
    She has us if she cares!

567
01:04:33.448 --> 01:04:37.585
Let's just take the twins
and run away. Christopher.

568
01:04:37.652 --> 01:04:42.055
We'll find a way out.
but let's do it now
before it's too late.

569
01:04:42.123 --> 01:04:44.124
        And then what do we do?

570
01:04:44.192 --> 01:04:48.562
            What do I do
            for the four of us
            to keep us alive?

571
01:04:48.630 --> 01:04:51.064
Don't you even doubt her
in the least?

572
01:04:51.132 --> 01:04:54.101
Can't you see how different
she's become?

573
01:04:54.168 --> 01:04:58.539
Can't you see
what wanting all that money
is doing to her?

574
01:05:00.308 --> 01:05:04.545
I can't stop
seeing that bed.

575
01:05:04.613 --> 01:05:07.981
            It's Mother. Cathy.

576
01:05:08.049 --> 01:05:10.584
            What do you
            want me to say?

577
01:05:12.420 --> 01:05:16.457
Just the truth.
that's all.

578
01:05:16.524 --> 01:05:18.525
[ Whimpering ]
    Cory?

579
01:05:18.593 --> 01:05:22.362
    I have to throw up. Cathy.

580
01:05:45.036 --> 01:05:48.972
[ Thunder Crashing ]

581
01:05:53.411 --> 01:05:55.478
[ Thunder Continues ]

582
01:06:05.190 --> 01:06:07.557
            [ Gasps ]

583
01:06:39.540 --> 01:06:44.844
Why are you taking
the flowers away.
Carrie?

584
01:06:44.912 --> 01:06:47.014
            'Cause it's time.

585
01:06:47.081 --> 01:06:50.650
            For what?
    Winter.

586
01:06:50.718 --> 01:06:52.719
        Do you have a headache.
        Cory?

587
01:06:52.786 --> 01:06:55.622
I had one yesterday.

588
01:06:55.689 --> 01:06:58.191
            Sore throat?
A little.

589
01:07:00.928 --> 01:07:03.497
            Any numbness
            in your fingers
            or your toes?

590
01:07:03.564 --> 01:07:05.598
What's numbness?

591
01:07:05.666 --> 01:07:08.801
        Like when your foot
        falls asleep
        and you can't feel it.

592
01:07:08.869 --> 01:07:11.071
Sometimes.

593
01:07:13.707 --> 01:07:15.775
        Let me see your hand.

594
01:07:17.678 --> 01:07:20.047
What are you doing?

595
01:07:20.114 --> 01:07:22.849
            Just looking.

596
01:07:22.917 --> 01:07:26.119
         <i>Darlings!  I'm back!</i>

597
01:07:27.272 --> 01:07:29.272
    Darlings!

598
01:07:29.341 --> 01:07:31.408
    I'm so happy.

599
01:07:31.476 --> 01:07:34.077
    Cathy. your hair!

600
01:07:34.145 --> 01:07:37.247
    What a sensible decision.
    It's lovely. sweetheart.

601
01:07:43.921 --> 01:07:47.641
    You're angry with me.
    But you don't know
    how much I've missed you.

602
01:07:47.708 --> 01:07:50.077
And wait till you see
the presents I've bought you.

603
01:07:50.145 --> 01:07:52.479
I wanted to tell you
 I was going away. but--

604
01:07:52.546 --> 01:07:55.082
        But guess.
        guess what's happened.

605
01:07:55.150 --> 01:07:58.218
    - The Grandfather's dead.
    - No.

606
01:07:58.286 --> 01:08:00.520
He's been taken
to the hospital?

607
01:08:00.588 --> 01:08:02.589
            No. I'm not happy
            because he's dying.

608
01:08:02.657 --> 01:08:05.558
            I'm happy because
            he loves me.

609
01:08:05.626 --> 01:08:07.627
            Don't you see?

610
01:08:07.695 --> 01:08:09.863
     <i>I've done what I promised.</i>

611
01:08:09.931 --> 01:08:13.533
I've pleased him so much
he's giving me a party tonight.

612
01:08:13.601 --> 01:08:19.106
         <i>A grand party</i>
         <i>to reintroduce me</i>
         <i>to society.</i>

613
01:08:19.174 --> 01:08:22.108
        And tomorrow my Father
        is having his attorney.

614
01:08:22.176 --> 01:08:24.611
        Bart Winslow.
        a wonderful man.

615
01:08:24.679 --> 01:08:27.481
        write me
        back into his will.

616
01:08:27.548 --> 01:08:29.549
        He's going to leave me
        everything.

617
01:08:29.617 --> 01:08:31.685
        Even this house.

618
01:08:31.753 --> 01:08:34.388
And what about
your children. Mother?
Does he know about them?

619
01:08:34.455 --> 01:08:37.223
    We know perfectly well
    what he feels about that.

620
01:08:37.292 --> 01:08:39.893
So what's to become of us. mom?

621
01:08:39.960 --> 01:08:42.962
How much longer
do we continue
living in this prison?

622
01:08:43.030 --> 01:08:47.334
    - Prison?
    - You come back
      with gifts for us. mom.

623
01:08:47.402 --> 01:08:49.636
Do you think
they can make up
for what we've lost?

624
01:08:49.704 --> 01:08:52.038
        Christopher...

625
01:08:52.106 --> 01:08:55.475
    - If you stop loving me--
    - I haven't stopped
      loving you. mom.

626
01:08:55.543 --> 01:09:00.213
I make myself keep loving you
every day despite what you do.

627
01:09:00.281 --> 01:09:03.634
    - Don't say another word.
    - Look at us. Mother.

628
01:09:03.701 --> 01:09:06.836
Do we look like you.
with your rosy cheeks
and your bright eyes?

629
01:09:06.904 --> 01:09:11.174
Look at the twins. Mother.
Cory has stomach cramps
almost every day!

630
01:09:11.242 --> 01:09:14.110
And Carrie has little sores
growing on her skin!

631
01:09:14.178 --> 01:09:18.114
Do you know. or even care.
that the Grandmother stopped
feeding us for over a week?

632
01:09:18.182 --> 01:09:22.753
    Stop it!
    You have no right
    to talk to me like that!

633
01:09:22.820 --> 01:09:26.623
    Tell me I've had pleasure
    while my children
    have been in pain.

634
01:09:26.691 --> 01:09:31.194
             <i>You are heartless.</i>

635
01:09:31.262 --> 01:09:37.033
        When you are ready
        to treat me with love.
        I'll be back.

636
01:10:05.363 --> 01:10:08.432
[ Scraping ]

637
01:10:12.303 --> 01:10:14.304
[ Scraping Continues ]

638
01:10:14.372 --> 01:10:16.373
            What are you doing?

639
01:10:16.441 --> 01:10:21.528
I'm going downstairs.
I wanna see that party.

640
01:10:21.596 --> 01:10:25.064
You going with me?

641
01:10:25.132 --> 01:10:29.986
♪ [ Waltz ]

642
01:10:39.129 --> 01:10:41.964
♪ [ Continues ]

643
01:12:05.483 --> 01:12:07.734
Why aren't you
up and dressed?

644
01:12:07.801 --> 01:12:11.605
What have I told you
about being together
in your night clothes?

645
01:12:11.672 --> 01:12:15.442
            Cory's sick.
            He's very sick.

646
01:12:15.509 --> 01:12:18.010
He needs a doctor.

647
01:12:24.352 --> 01:12:26.353
[ Door Locking ]

648
01:12:44.405 --> 01:12:47.473
[ Cory Gasping ]

649
01:12:57.451 --> 01:12:59.202
        Why are you
        just standing there?

650
01:12:59.270 --> 01:13:02.973
    Cory needs to be taken
    to a hospital.  There's
    no other decision to make.

651
01:13:03.041 --> 01:13:06.043
     <i>What's wrong with you.</i>
     <i>Mother?</i>

652
01:13:06.110 --> 01:13:08.411
     Are you just
     gonna stand there
     and think about yourself...

653
01:13:08.479 --> 01:13:11.314
        and your money
        while Cory lies there
        and dies?

654
01:13:11.382 --> 01:13:13.817
Don't you care
what happens to him?

655
01:13:13.885 --> 01:13:16.586
        Have you forgotten
        that you're his Mother?

656
01:13:16.654 --> 01:13:19.255
        Always it's you!

657
01:13:19.323 --> 01:13:21.324
                        Ooh!
    Cathy!

658
01:13:21.392 --> 01:13:25.162
    Damn you to hell mama.
    if you don't take Cory
    to a hospital right now!

659
01:13:25.229 --> 01:13:27.430
Do you think you can go on
doing whatever you want to us...

660
01:13:27.498 --> 01:13:29.566
and nobody will
ever find out?

661
01:13:29.633 --> 01:13:33.170
If Cory dies. mama.
you'll pay for it.

662
01:13:33.237 --> 01:13:37.074
One way or another.
I will find a way.

663
01:13:37.141 --> 01:13:39.710
I promise you that.

664
01:13:42.363 --> 01:13:45.398
                        Come in.

665
01:13:45.466 --> 01:13:47.734
    Take the child downstairs
    and bring the car around.

666
01:13:47.802 --> 01:13:51.237
    My daughter is taking him
    to the hospital.

667
01:14:07.921 --> 01:14:10.357
Hello. John.

668
01:14:32.946 --> 01:14:37.517
            Don't worry. Fred.
            He'll be back.

669
01:14:37.584 --> 01:14:40.553
[ Shovel Digging ]

670
01:15:35.443 --> 01:15:38.144
Cory had pneumonia.

671
01:15:38.211 --> 01:15:40.212
The doctors did all they could.

672
01:15:40.280 --> 01:15:43.200
There won't be a funeral.
He's already been buried.

673
01:15:43.267 --> 01:15:45.335
                No!

674
01:16:23.224 --> 01:16:25.825
Something's wrong
with Fred. Christopher.

675
01:16:25.892 --> 01:16:29.395
He won't wake up.

676
01:17:40.717 --> 01:17:42.852
[ Christopher ]
Arsenic poisoning.

677
01:17:42.920 --> 01:17:44.921
In the sugar on the cookies.

678
01:17:44.989 --> 01:17:49.059
In small quantities
you can't taste it or smell it.

679
01:17:51.595 --> 01:17:54.164
It doesn't leave
much of a trace. Cathy.

680
01:17:54.231 --> 01:17:56.599
If they did an autopsy
they wouldn't have found it.

681
01:17:56.667 --> 01:17:59.135
Unless they were
looking for it.

682
01:17:59.203 --> 01:18:01.271
                What do we do?

683
01:18:01.339 --> 01:18:05.741
Tonight I'll go downstairs
by myself.

684
01:18:05.809 --> 01:18:07.810
I'm gonna find us
some money...

685
01:18:07.878 --> 01:18:10.663
or a couple of those
diamond rings
that Grandmother wears.

686
01:18:10.730 --> 01:18:13.232
                And then what?

687
01:18:13.300 --> 01:18:16.302
Then we're gonna leave
this place. Cathy.

688
01:18:16.369 --> 01:18:19.271
One way or another
we're getting out.

689
01:18:19.339 --> 01:18:23.443
Whatever happens after that
will be up to us.

690
01:18:25.128 --> 01:18:28.914
But whatever happens
we'll be free.

691
01:18:51.939 --> 01:18:54.240
[ Door Opening ]

692
01:19:05.853 --> 01:19:07.620
Do we really have to wait
until tomorrow?

693
01:19:07.687 --> 01:19:09.688
                Yes.

694
01:19:09.756 --> 01:19:12.024
Don't know if I can.
            You must.

695
01:19:12.092 --> 01:19:15.228
[ Bart ]
What difference
would 12 hours make?

696
01:19:15.295 --> 01:19:19.198
        The difference between
        one ring and two.

697
01:19:22.653 --> 01:19:25.788
        Damn you!

698
01:19:25.856 --> 01:19:28.624
[ Thumping ]
Damn you!

699
01:19:28.926 --> 01:19:32.145
        What happened?
        You found a way out?
We're leaving tomorrow.  Yeah.

700
01:19:32.212 --> 01:19:33.863
            Where?  A window?
No. a door.

701
01:19:33.930 --> 01:19:36.065
The front door.
                    What?

702
01:19:36.133 --> 01:19:38.134
There's gonna be another
party tomorrow.

703
01:19:38.201 --> 01:19:40.603
I saw them preparing
one of the rooms.

704
01:19:40.671 --> 01:19:43.573
There's probably gonna be
100 guests. maybe more.

705
01:19:43.641 --> 01:19:46.509
They can't keep locking
the door. not with
that many people coming in.

706
01:19:46.577 --> 01:19:48.811
[ Panting ]

707
01:19:48.879 --> 01:19:51.748
    What else happened tonight.
    Christopher?
    What else did you see?

708
01:19:53.651 --> 01:19:55.685
    I mean. you told me
    that it's us against them.

709
01:19:55.753 --> 01:19:59.955
            We're on our own.
            Don't lie to me.
            Christopher.

710
01:20:01.458 --> 01:20:04.827
It's not just a party. Cathy.
 It's a wedding party.

711
01:20:04.895 --> 01:20:08.714
Mom's getting married
to that man tomorrow.

712
01:21:07.724 --> 01:21:10.359
                Aah!
                [ Grunting ]

713
01:21:10.794 --> 01:21:13.112
         <i>[ Cathy ]</i>
         <i>No. Chris!</i>

714
01:21:14.114 --> 01:21:16.299
        [ Panting ]
        Aah!

715
01:21:19.637 --> 01:21:21.638
        We're very excited
        to be here today.

716
01:21:21.705 --> 01:21:23.773
        Congratulations.

717
01:21:27.044 --> 01:21:30.096
[ Carrie ]
I'm scared. Christopher.

718
01:21:30.164 --> 01:21:33.732
There's nothing to be afraid of.
Nobody's gonna hurt us anymore.

719
01:21:36.136 --> 01:21:38.137
                    This way.
No. Chris.

720
01:21:38.205 --> 01:21:41.707
They're not gonna get away
with this.  We gotta go tell
our Grandfather the truth.

721
01:21:41.775 --> 01:21:43.776
    What difference does it make
    now?  Let's just go!
No!

722
01:21:43.843 --> 01:21:47.046
Mother's not getting
that money. not after
the way she treated us.

723
01:21:47.114 --> 01:21:49.615
Now. come on.

724
01:22:21.565 --> 01:22:24.132
        He's gone.

725
01:22:24.200 --> 01:22:27.069
            He's dead. Cathy.

726
01:22:28.104 --> 01:22:31.474
Yea. we can be
with mama now.

727
01:22:31.908 --> 01:22:36.095
    No. Carrie.
    Mama lied to us.

728
01:22:36.162 --> 01:22:39.699
She said she'd come and get us
after her Father died. but...

729
01:22:39.766 --> 01:22:43.803
    she never came.

730
01:22:43.871 --> 01:22:47.540
        She only cares
        about herself. Carrie.

731
01:22:49.109 --> 01:22:52.244
    She's going to spoil
    everything.

732
01:22:52.312 --> 01:22:54.313
    We can't wait any longer.

733
01:22:54.381 --> 01:22:57.750
        But your Mother--
        These are her friends.

734
01:22:57.818 --> 01:23:00.252
    It's <i>my</i> wedding.

735
01:23:00.320 --> 01:23:02.855
We'll start the ceremony now!

736
01:23:26.663 --> 01:23:28.931
Today's April 23.

737
01:23:33.837 --> 01:23:36.605
Christopher. what is it?

738
01:23:36.673 --> 01:23:41.610
        A copy of
        the Grandfather's will.
        It's two months old.

739
01:23:41.678 --> 01:23:45.314
        Says if it's ever proven
        that mom had children
        from her first marriage.

740
01:23:45.381 --> 01:23:50.085
        even after he's dead.
        she'll be disinherited.

741
01:23:50.153 --> 01:23:53.355
Mother's known all this time
that we could never be found.

742
01:23:53.423 --> 01:23:56.725
        She never meant for us
        to leave that attic.

743
01:23:56.977 --> 01:24:01.397
♪ [ "Wedding March" ]

744
01:24:26.506 --> 01:24:29.575
        Dearly beloved.
        family and friends.

745
01:24:29.643 --> 01:24:33.212
        we are gathered here
        on this most joyous
        of occasions...

746
01:24:33.280 --> 01:24:37.883
to join Corrine and Bart
in holy matrimony.

747
01:24:37.951 --> 01:24:40.035
        Let us pray.

748
01:24:43.507 --> 01:24:47.877
Heavenly Father.
we read in Genesis
the creation story.

749
01:24:47.944 --> 01:24:51.547
You said it was not good
for man to be alone.

750
01:24:51.615 --> 01:24:56.452
so you created woman
and thus gave your blessing
to the union of holy matrimony.

751
01:24:56.520 --> 01:25:00.222
        Look now upon
        Bart and Corrine...

752
01:25:00.290 --> 01:25:02.792
and pour out
your grace upon them.

753
01:25:02.860 --> 01:25:06.295
Give them the strength
and peace to honor the vows
they make before you today.

754
01:25:06.363 --> 01:25:10.767
    We pray that.
    in your loving kindness.

755
01:25:10.934 --> 01:25:12.818
you would bless their home
by filling it with the sounds...

756
01:25:12.886 --> 01:25:15.888
of happy. healthy children.

757
01:25:15.955 --> 01:25:18.457
In the name
of Christ. amen.

758
01:25:21.861 --> 01:25:24.697
                Mother!

759
01:25:27.367 --> 01:25:29.919
Do you like my dress?

760
01:25:29.986 --> 01:25:33.155
I thought it was appropriate
for the occasion.

761
01:25:33.223 --> 01:25:36.392
    Who are you?
    How did you get in here?

762
01:25:36.460 --> 01:25:38.561
        Have you forgotten us
        already?

763
01:25:38.629 --> 01:25:41.397
    Mama?

764
01:25:41.465 --> 01:25:44.967
    - Who are you children?
    - We're the children
      of the bride.

765
01:25:45.035 --> 01:25:49.104
    Nonsense.  You know
    I don't have any children.

766
01:25:49.172 --> 01:25:51.157
        Get them out of here.

767
01:25:51.224 --> 01:25:54.860
        I'll not have
        my wedding day ruined
        by a cruel. evil prank.

768
01:25:54.928 --> 01:25:57.096
You're the one who's
cruel and evil. Mother.

769
01:25:57.164 --> 01:25:59.165
    You kept us locked up
    in that attic...

770
01:25:59.232 --> 01:26:01.567
    and you said
    you'd come for us
    after your Father died.

771
01:26:01.634 --> 01:26:04.336
You never came!
[ Christopher ]
You couldn't let anybody...

772
01:26:04.404 --> 01:26:07.840
find out about us
'cause if you did
you'd be disinherited.

773
01:26:07.908 --> 01:26:11.276
                It's not true.
                No!

774
01:26:11.344 --> 01:26:13.412
    What proof do they have?

775
01:26:13.747 --> 01:26:18.650
- It died from eating
  the same cookies Cory ate.
- Who's Cory?

776
01:26:18.719 --> 01:26:21.653
        He was your son
        and my little brother.
        And you killed him.

777
01:26:21.722 --> 01:26:25.758
Just like you tried to kill us.
Look at us. Mother!

778
01:26:25.826 --> 01:26:29.028
        How could you
        do this to us?

779
01:26:29.229 --> 01:26:32.380
    Here. Mother.
    Our wedding present to you.

780
01:26:32.448 --> 01:26:35.884
                        Stop it.
Go on. eat it!

781
01:26:35.952 --> 01:26:38.955
Eat the cookie!

782
01:26:39.022 --> 01:26:42.124
                [ Grunting ]

783
01:26:45.879 --> 01:26:48.114
[ Screaming ]

784
01:27:20.531 --> 01:27:23.699
[ Narrator ]
We finally got our real revenge.

785
01:27:23.767 --> 01:27:25.968
We managed to make it
on our own.

786
01:27:26.036 --> 01:27:28.971
I got a job to help put Chris
through medical school.

787
01:27:29.039 --> 01:27:33.175
Little Carrie grew up but
she was never truly healthy.

788
01:27:33.243 --> 01:27:36.378
I even started dancing again.

789
01:27:36.446 --> 01:27:40.416
We left the past behind.
all except the memories...

790
01:27:40.483 --> 01:27:45.421
of Mother. Grandmother
and the attic.

791
01:27:45.488 --> 01:27:48.858
I sometimes wonder
if Grandmother is still alive.

792
01:27:48.926 --> 01:27:51.761
Still presiding over
Foxworth Hall.

793
01:27:51.828 --> 01:27:54.430
Still awaiting my return.

793
